Subject: Re: [VB] Rear shift rod coupler replacement

On Tue, Nov 30, 2004 at 03:18:50PM -0500, rob wrote:
> 	In the Bentley - this procedure for removing the rear shift
> 	rod coupling calls for removing the engine & tranny.  My shift
> 	raod coupler is in a pretty precarous state and needs to be
> 	replaced.  I loosened it up and it almost looks as if it could
> 	be removed if maybe I removed the front shift rod and slid the
> 	rod up? 

I was able in my 66 to replace it w/ all parts still installed. IIRC I
did have to disconnect the front end of the shift rod (under the front
of the bus) so that I had enough room. Then just loosened the set
screws, replace the coupling and install in reverse (do be sure to
include safety wire).

